A mix between their mother and father. Like Etsuji, she had bright amber eyes. They glowed brought in light. Brighter than his ever would. Her skin closely matching their father too. Etsuji was really the only one who matched his mother in that regard. She would flip through her book, a small smile on her face. (edited)
looks off to a garden. He sees her. His mother. Her matching honey skin, akin to his own. Her lushness black hair, flowing in the wind like leaves on a tree. Her kind, soft black eyes. He missed the real her. She was smelling the flowers she had planted only recently. A warm smile on her face. He remembers being wrapped up in her arms. How it felt to be in her embrace. She taught him kindness. She taught him so much… and yet he had forgotten. How could he have forgotten? He saw the joy. The joy they all had when he was away. When it was just the five of them. The peace. The serenity. He misses this. He wishes he still had this…
Before he could take a step towards any of them, he brought back to reality. He took deep breath, closing his eyes. When he opened them again… She was gone. Her. They were both gone now. The truth about his father, and the lies about his mother. Both had stopped. Finally stopped. Their whispers were gone. He hopes for good. He truly does. With a weak, yet warm, smile, he says, “Th…Thank you…”
